adbYwHrHjXFdEcF8MAeG1xGr2Y3FGaAEme2njvi1WMjVsEjOAM_zaM5K90HJSbPQrraFdC411VdKRD2Ct1OnTNWApOiZdMDyHSKYWGQK0CF1pPMzDhxlqTjqSK3STT29EosxLqGs-_EHwqs0FTzGR6yl9KwcN2dPNOdj52Qeic7dlWe9gvc=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating coverage and assertion**\\n\\nI'm thinking that running coverage might utilize the JVM agent, which could count a call site as covered if an exception is caught right before it. But wait, should I remove the previous assertion? It didn’t seem to help, but maybe it’s worth considering for the final version. I’m wondering if it’s possible to add or refine tests to ensure execution reaches that point; if not, that would lead to the unacceptable status of “No viable patch.”\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "I inspected the remaining `Reflector#getObjectProperty` path and refined the existing test to document the version-specific blocker.\n\nThe remaining call site at `Reflector.java:475` is not reachable through the public API in `plexus-utils:1.0-alpha-3`:\n\n```java\nObject returnValue = getField(targetClass, propertyName, true);\n```\n\nHere `targetClass` is itself a `Class` object, so `Reflector#getField(...)` looks up the property on `Class.class` before reaching:\n\n```java\nmethod.invoke(target, new Object[]{});\n```\n\nSince `Class.class` exposes no public fields, `getField(...)` throws `ReflectorException` with `NoSuchFieldException` first. The accessor method is found, but cannot be invoked.\n\nUpdated test file:\n\n- `tests/src/plexus/plexus-utils/1.0-alpha-3/src/test/java/plexus/plexus_utils/ReflectorTest.java`\n\nThe test now asserts that the accessor is not called, proving the public path fails before the uncovered `Method.invoke` site.\n\nI did not run tests, per workflow instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03ae9c066e71ff8a016a3e905cd6008195b13fe978851565ea\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 31879, "output"